REST

This is a KSH shell built-in command that causes the shell to wait for the
specified amount of time (given as the argument) before continuing.

Synopsis:
$ rest <timespec> [-af <afile>] [-o <opt(s)>] [-V]

Arguments:
<timespec>	a specification of the amount of time to rest
-af <afile>	argument-list file
-o <opt(s)>	options: poll, intpoll
-V		print command version to standard-error and then exit

